33:47.414 --> 33:49.997
Jesus Christ died on that cross 2000 years ago.

33:50.057 --> 33:52.600
His body was broken so we could be healed.

33:53.160 --> 33:56.064
His blood was shed so we could have forgiveness of our sins.

33:56.884 --> 33:58.226
And Jesus told us

33:58.338 --> 34:04.325
to do this when we get together with the bread and the wine focusing on his sacrifice for us.

34:04.826 --> 34:07.769
But the Bible says, before you take it, we should all examine ourselves.

34:08.210 --> 34:12.975
So let's bow our heads and let me pray a prayer of forgiveness over all of us who are here.

34:13.776 --> 34:20.804
Heavenly Father, before we partake of the bread in the cup this morning and in obedience to the scriptures, we pause to examine ourselves.

34:21.605 --> 34:25.650
If we have sinned against you in thought word or deed by what we've done,

34:26.146 --> 34:28.849
by what we've left undone, something we should have done, we didn't.

34:29.970 --> 34:41.761
If we haven't loved you with our whole heart, if we haven't loved our neighbors as ourselves, for the sake of your beloved son Jesus, who gave himself as a sacrifice for our sins, we pray, have mercy on us, and forgive us of all our sins.

34:42.382 --> 34:46.266
Strengthen us, and by the power of your Holy Spirit, keep us in eternal life.

34:47.567 --> 34:51.110
Now, heads are bound, people are praying and reflecting, examining themselves.

34:51.631 --> 34:54.834
Maybe you're here this morning, and you've never really

34:55.970 --> 34:57.272
taken part of faith.

34:58.133 --> 35:01.077
You hear us singing, you see us doing what we're doing.

35:01.097 --> 35:04.761
People sacrificing the kind of money they're sacrificing.

35:04.781 --> 35:05.502
